Key Match Events: Travis Head scored a century in the World Cup final
India were made to work for every run due to tight bowling and aggressive fielding
Post-Match Reflections: Rohit Sharma expressed disappointment about the missed opportunity
Pat Cummins expressed pride in the team's performance and called it the top of the mountain
Miscellaneous Highlights: Australia won the World Cup for the sixth time
India played in their backyard and were the best team in the tournament
Others: The pitch proved to be slow
India looked to threaten a comeback after rocking Australia for 47 for 3
Head and Marnus Labuschagne put their heads down to construct a match-turning 192-run partnership
